&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:-27.0pt;text-align:justify'>&lt;b>&lt;span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>     &lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt'>I. Unleavened
Elements&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:-27.0pt;text-align:justify'>&lt;span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:-27.0pt;text-align:justify'>&lt;span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>            In regard to the nature of the elements of
the Lord’s Supper, the basic fact is that Jesus instituted it during a Passover
meal. Consequently, he used elements available at that feast.&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>FREQUENCY OF OBSERVING THE LORD</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/communion/frequency-of-observing-the-lord/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/communion/frequency-of-observing-the-lord/</guid><description>&lt;style>
